{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Downtown West |native_name = <!-- for neighborhoods whose native name is not in English --> |nickname = |settlement_type = [[Neighborhoods of Minneapolis|Neighborhood]] |motto = |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_flag = |image_seal = |image_shield = |image_map = MinneapolisDowntownWestNeighborhood.PNG |mapsize = 200px |map_caption = Location of Downtown West within the U.S. city of [[Minneapolis]] |subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] |subdivision_type1= [[U.S. state|State]] |subdivision_type2= [[List of counties in Minnesota|County]] |subdivision_type3= [[List of cities in Minnesota|City]] |subdivision_type4= [[Neighborhoods of Minneapolis|Community]] |subdivision_name= United States |subdivision_name1= [[Minnesota]] |subdivision_name2= [[Hennepin County, Minnesota|Hennepin]] |subdivision_name3= [[Minneapolis]] |subdivision_name4= [[Central, Minneapolis|Central]] |established= Founded |established_date= 1849 |area_magnitude = |unit_pref = US |area_total_sq_mi = 0.759 |area_land_sq_mi = |area_water_sq_mi = |area_water_percent = |area_footnotes = <ref name=citydata>{{cite web | title=Downtown West neighborhood in Minneapolis, Minnesota (MN), 55401, 55402, 55403, 55404, 55415 detailed profile | url=http://www.city-data.com/neighborhood/Downtown-West-Minneapolis-MN.html | date=2011 | publisher=[[City-Data]] | accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref> |population_as_of = 2010 |population_total = 5,781 |population_density_sq_mi = auto |population_footnotes=<ref name=population-mncompass>{{cite web | title=Minneapolis Neighborhood Profile: Downtown West | url=http://www.mncompass.org/_pdfs/neighborhood-profiles/Minneapolis-DowntownWest-102011.pdf | format=PDF | date=October 2011 | publisher=Minnesota Compass | accessdate=2013-11-12}}</ref> |timezone= [[North American Central Time Zone|CST]] |utc_offset= -6 |timezone_DST= [[North American Central Time Zone|CDT]] |utc_offset_DST= -5 |coordinates = |elevation_m= |elevation_ft= |postal_code_type = ZIP code |postal_code = 55401, 55402, 55403, 55404, 55415, 55487 |area_code = [[area code 612|612]] |website = |footnotes = |demographics = <!-- enter template using {{US Census tract embedded}} --> }} <!-- Infobox ends --> {{USCensusPop |1980= 3522 |1990= 3789 |2000= 4581 |2010= 5781 }} '''Downtown West''' is an official neighborhood in [[Minneapolis]], part of the larger [[Central, Minneapolis|Central community]]. It is the heart of downtown Minneapolis (and Minneapolis as a whole), containing the bulk of high-rise office buildings in the city, and is what comes to mind when most Minneapolitans think of "downtown". Its boundaries are as follows (going in a clockwise direction): 12th Street to the southwest, 3rd Avenue North, Washington Avenue North, and [[Hennepin Avenue]] to the northwest, the [[Mississippi River]] to the northeast, and Portland Avenue, 5th Street South, and 5th Avenue South to the southeast. It is bordered by the [[North Loop, Minneapolis|North Loop]], [[Nicollet Island/East Bank, Minneapolis|Nicollet Island/East Bank]], [[Downtown East, Minneapolis|Downtown East]], [[Elliot Park, Minneapolis|Elliot Park]], and [[Loring Park, Minneapolis|Loring Park]] neighborhoods. Downtown West is home to most of Minneapolis's most notable buildings like the [[Foshay Tower]] and [[IDS Center]]. Being next to the neighborhood [[Loring Park, Minneapolis|Loring Park]] which has a substantial population of gay people, it is unsurprising that Downtown West has a few gay bars such as [[The Saloon, Minneapolis|The Saloon]]. {{Coord|44.9741|-93.2732|region:US-MN_type:city(4581)_source:GoogleEarth|display=title|notes=<ref>''Downtown West, Minneapolis, MN.'' [[Google Earth]]. Retrieved 2011-03-09.</ref>}}
