{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox company | name = flok | logo = File:Flok official logo.png | type = [[Subsidiary]] | foundation = {{start date and age|2011}} | location = [[New York City]] | industry = [[Mobile computing|Mobile]], [[Mobile app|App]]s, [[Chatbots]], Loyalty Programs | parent = [[Wix.com]] | homepage = {{url|http://flok.com}} }}
'''flok''' (formerly Loyalblocks)<ref>{{cite news|title=Your next loyalty ‘punch card’ will be driven by AI|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/04/07/your-next-loyalty-punch-card-will-be-driven-by-ai/|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[VentureBeat]]}}</ref> is an American [[tech startup]] based in [[New York City]] that provides marketing solutions such as [[chatbots]]/[[AI]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Flok uses Bluetooth and chatbots to lure people inside thousands of small businesses|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/07/26/flok-uses-bluetooth-and-chatbots-to-lure-people-inside-thousands-of-small-businesses/|publisher=[[VentureBeat]]|accessdate=27 July 2016}}</ref> customer loyalty programs, [[mobile apps]] and [[Customer relationship management|CRM]] services to local businesses.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Council|first1=Forbes Communications|title=How Conversational UX And The Internet Of Things Are Changing The Way We Communicate|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbescommunicationscouncil/2016/07/06/how-conversational-ux-and-the-internet-of-things-are-changing-the-way-we-communicate/#60c8184a249e|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Should Your Business Create an App?|url=https://www.americanexpress.com/us/small-business/openforum/articles/business-create-an-app/|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[American Express]] OPEN Forum|date=25 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Small Business Loyalty Programs : flok|url=http://www.trendhunter.com/trends/flok|publisher=Trend Hunter|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Loyalty Is Not Enough — It’s All About Customer Relationship Management Now|url=http://www.geomarketing.com/loyalty-is-not-enough-its-all-about-customer-relationship-management-now|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[Geomarketing]]|date=7 June 2016}}</ref>
In January 2017, the company was acquired by [[Wix.com]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/01/19/wix-buys-flok-to-add-loyalty-and-mobile-crm-to-its-suite-of-business-tools/|title=Wix buys Flok to add loyalty and mobile CRM to its business tools|last=Lunden|first=Ingrid|date=19 January 2017|website=[[TechCrunch]]|publisher=|access-date=23 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-wix-acquires-israeli-crm-co-flok-1001173124|title=Wix acquires Israeli CRM co flok - Globes|website=Globes|language=he|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>
==Background== flok was founded in 2011 by Ido Gaver and Eran Kirshenboim and has offices in [[Tel Aviv]], [[Israel]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zimmerman|first1=Eilene|title=LoyalBlocks Simplifies Mobile App Creation for Small Merchants|url=http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/16/loyalblocks-simplifies-mobile-app-creation-for-small-merchants/?_r=1|accessdate=26 July 2016|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> In May 2013, flok secured a $9 million Series A Round from [[General Catalyst Partners]] with participation from Founder Collective and existing investor Gemini Israel Ventures.<ref>https://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/05/23/nyc-based-loyalblocks-raises-9m-for-its-automated-mobile-loyalty-program/#gref</ref> In total, flok has raised over $18 million in [[venture capital]] in three rounds.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Taylor|first1=Colleen|title=LoyalBlocks Lands $9 Million Led By General Catalyst To Scale Out Its Mobile-Based Loyalty Program|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/05/23/loyalblocks-9-million-funding/|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Flok company profile on CrunchBase|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/loyalblocks#/entity|publisher=[[CrunchBase]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Your next loyalty ‘punch card’ will be driven by AI|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/04/07/your-next-loyalty-punch-card-will-be-driven-by-ai|publisher=[[VentureBeat]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
In May 2014, flok announced a self-service loyalty platform for SMBs to build their own programs with beacon integration. At that time, approximately 40,000 businesses were using the service.<ref>http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/225373/loyalblocks-adds-beacon-to-self-serve-loyalty-plat.html</ref> In 2016, flok released a turnkey chatbot service for local businesses,<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2016/07/26/flok-uses-bluetooth-and-chatbots-to-lure-people-inside-thousands-of-small-businesses/</ref><ref>http://marketingland.com/flok-wants-bring-chatbots-small-business-masses-186056</ref> and was featured in [[AdWeek]] for developing the first "weed bot" chatbot for a [[California]] [[cannabis]] business.<ref>{{cite web|title=This California Marijuana Dispensary Is Using Bots to Understand Customers' Preferences|url=http://www.adweek.com/news/technology/california-marijuana-dispensary-using-bots-understand-customers-preferences-172238|publisher=[[Adweek]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
==Services== flok offers an eponymous customer-facing app<ref>{{cite web|title=flok - get rewarded on the App Store|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/flok-get-rewarded/id376560037?mt=8|publisher=[[App Store (iOS)]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref> that consumers use to receive rewards and deals form partner businesses,<ref>http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/startup-loyalblocks-helps-small-businesses-zap-deals-rewards-customers-smartphones-article-1.1154135</ref> and a flok business app for merchants to manage the platform.<ref>{{cite web|title=flok business on the App Store|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/flok-business/id1102450236?mt=8|publisher=[[App Store (iOS)]]|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref> Both are available for iOS and Android operating systems. flok's main products center around customer loyalty and rewards. The platform offers a digital punch card, [[proximity marketing]], push messaging and CRM services in addition to its chatbots and AI features.<ref>http://streetfightmag.com/2016/07/26/flok-launches-chatbots-to-bolster-customer-engagement-for-local-businesses/</ref>
flok provides partner businesses with [[beacons]] that can locate customers and verify store visits.<ref>{{cite web|title=Beacons 101: What Smart Brick-and-Mortar Retailers Need to Know {{!}} Payment Week|url=http://paymentweek.com/2016-5-17-beacons-101-what-smart-brick-and-mortar-retailers-need-to-know-10534/|publisher=Payment Week|accessdate=26 July 2016|date=17 May 2016}}</ref> As of July 2016, flok had a 4-star rating on Merchant Maverick review site.<ref>{{cite web|title=Flok Review - Merchant Maverick|url=https://www.merchantmaverick.com/reviews/flok-review/|publisher=Merchant Maverick|accessdate=26 July 2016}}</ref>
