'''Serge Kampf''' (October 13, 1934 – March 15, 2016) was a French businessman who founded the computer services company [[Capgemini]] in 1967.

==Biography==
Serge Kampf served as Managing Director of Cap Gemini EUROPE BV and Cap Gemini Benelux BV.

Kampf served as Chief Executive Officer of Cap Gemini SA, Cap Gemini Service SA, Cap Sogeti SA, Cap Sogeti.Com SA. 

He founded Capgemini U.S. LLC. 

He founded Sogeti USA, LLC in 1967. 

He founded Capgemini UK plc in 1967 and served as its Chairman. 

Kampf served as Chairman of Cap Gemini SA, Capgemini Suisse S.A., Capgemini Service S.A.S., Cap Sogeti SA, Cap Sogeti. Com SA., Cap Gemini (Suisse) SA and Cap Gemini ERNST & YOUNG (SUISSE) SA. 

He served as Chairman of the Board of Cap gemini U.S. LLC. 

Kampf served as a Director of Cap Gemini SA, Cap Gemini Telecom SA, Cap Gemini Gouvieux SA, Cap Gemini France SA, Cap Sogeti France SA, Cap Gemini AMERICA INC. (USA), CGA TRANSMILLENNIUM, INC. (USA), Cap Gemini ERNST & YOUNG UK, PLC and Cap Gemini UK, PLC. 

He was a permanent representative of Cap Gemini SA on the Board of Directors of Cap Gemini ERNST & YOUNG Université SA. He served as a Director of Capgemini North America, Inc. 

He served as an Independent Director of Sanofi-Aventis SA from August 2004 to October 30, 2007. 

Kampf served as a Member of the Supervisory Board of Sanofi-Aventis AG from December 15, 1999 to August 30, 2004.

